# Rust
# Use **/target (not target/) so nested build artifacts are excluded too —
# e.g. module-templates/*/target/ from local WASM builds can be 3 GB+.
# Without this, those trees enter the build context and trigger an OOM/ENOSPC
# failure when `chown -R /app` traverses them in Docker Desktop's VM.
**/target
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Frontend
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
frontend/.vite/

# Git
.git/
.gitignore

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log

# Environment — broad on purpose. Both Dockerfiles do `COPY . .` and
# nothing under controller/ or worker/ build-time references .env files,
# so blocking everything that matches .env* is safe and prevents a
# .env.production (or similar) from accidentally landing in an image
# layer where `docker history` would expose it.
.env*

# Private keys, certificates, credential blobs. Defense-in-depth — these
# should never be in the source tree, but if one slips in we don't want
# it baked into a published image layer.
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.cer
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
*.keystore
credentials*.json
*credentials.json

# Release artifacts that are produced by `make release` itself. Including
# the previous run's digests in the next build context is harmless but
# pointless and busts the COPY layer cache on every release.
release-digests.txt

# Agent worktrees (claude-code, codex). These contain duplicate copies of
# the workspace from in-progress agent runs — bloats build context, busts
# COPY layer cache, and ships nested `.git` dirs into intermediate stages.
.claude/
.codex/

# Documentation, observability dashboards, and dev-only scripts —
# nothing the controller or worker binaries need at runtime.
docs/
observability/
add_scopes.py
update_protocol.py

# Lint configs consumed by CI / dev only.
audit.toml
deny.toml

# Helm chart / k3s deploy assets — not part of the controller/worker
# build context. Helm renders against the chart from the operator's
# checkout, not from the published image.
deploy/

# CHANGELOG, AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md — docs, not runtime.
CHANGELOG.md
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
